{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "Nomad server construction and shutdown lifecycle", "note": "pinned nomad/server.go:744 Shutdown, :805 IsShutdown, :815 Leave, :336 NewServer via the called_by edge — all cited directly in Step 2"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "composed_by gave ~40 direct *Server holders with file:line (nomad/acl_endpoint.go:65, nomad/worker.go:92, nomad/drainer_shims.go:14, command/agent/agent.go:73), plus includes (rpcHandler nomad/rpc.go:47, planner nomad/plan_apply.go:24, nodeHeartbeater nomad/heartbeat.go:37) — the backbone of Step 4 Group A"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "retained_via_interfaces was the single highest-value result: volumewatcher.Watcher/volumeWatcher via CSIVolumeRPC, drainer.NodeDrainer via RaftApplier, PeriodicDispatch via JobEvalDispatcher, the three schedulers via Planner, auth.Authenticator via Encrypter, client-side RPCer holders — with carrier and chain. This is Steps 4B/5 nearly wholesale."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "completed composed_by beyond the truncated graph call (Operator, Periodic, Plan, Region, Scaling, Search, ServiceRegistration, StatsFetcher, Status, System, TaskGroupHostVolumeClaim, Variables) and separated test holders (testcluster, tlsTestHelper)"}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "raftutil.FSMHelper listed as retained via chain nomad.nomadFSM > nomad.Encrypter > nomad.Server — false for the live server; reading helper/raftutil/fsm.go:84 showed it is the offline debug FSM built by dummyFSM. I reported it as a disclosed false positive."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "client-side RPCer holders (allocRunner, csiHook, widmgr.Signer, remotePrevAlloc) presented with chain 'agent.Agent > nomad.Server' as if live; grep showed client/config/config.go:161 RPCHandler is assigned only in *_test.go, so the route is inert in production. The chain is declared-containment, not runtime-verified — the note says so, but the framing overstates it."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "missed deploymentwatcher entirely from retained_via_interfaces — Watcher.raft (deployments_watcher.go:76), deploymentRPC/jobRPC (:82,:85), batcher.go:20, and the three embedded fields in deployment_watcher.go. That is the Tier-1 risk of the whole ticket, and it is invisible because deploymentWatcherRaftShim stores a bound method value s.raftApply rather than a struct field."},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.Server", "note": "truncated with omitted_edges 111 while reporting completeness verdict 'complete' — the composed_by list was cut off mid-way (ended at NodePool), so acting on it alone would have missed a dozen holders"}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "truncated composed_by; I ran a regex for '*Server'-typed struct fields across nomad/ and command/ to get an independent count. It returned exactly 52 production holders, matching blast — that cross-check is what let me state the audit was exhaustive."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "read", "missing": "no field-level line numbers — every retained_via_interfaces row pointed at the struct's start line, not the retaining field. For Step 4/5 I needed 'the field', so I grepped for the field declarations to get drainer.go:159, volumes_watcher.go:26, auth.go:64, generic_sched.go:57, signer.go:41, etc."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no assignment/binding sites — the response tells you who holds an interface but not where the concrete value is stored. I grepped/read nomad/server.go:1160-1199, worker.go:628, volume_watcher.go:63, client.go:462/2959/3005 to build the Step 5 routes."},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no deploymentwatcher rows at all; I found that subsystem only by grepping 'interface {' in nomad/deploymentwatcher/ after noticing setupDeploymentWatcher in the server.go boot sequence"},
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "Nomad server construction and shutdown lifecycle", "fallback": "read", "missing": "symbol locations only, no bodies — I read nomad/server.go:336-586 and :744-802 to describe the boot ordering and what Shutdown does and does not stop, which was the substance of Step 2"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "nomad.Server", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no way to distinguish live vs dormant routes; I grepped 'RPCHandler[:=]' repo-wide to establish the client chain is test-only, and 'PlanBuilder{' to establish PlanBuilder.Planner is nil in production"}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query_before": "sense_graph nomad.Server (returned truncated:true, omitted_edges:111, next_steps suggesting sense_blast)", "query_after": "sense_blast nomad.Server with include_tests:false, max_hops:3", "hint": "'51 callers found — check blast radius before changing this symbol' plus truncated/omitted_edges — this pushed me to blast, which is where retained_via_interfaces came from and is the reason I found the narrowed holders at all"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query_before": "trusting the composed_by/retained lists as the audit", "query_after": "regex grep for '*Server'-typed struct fields across nomad/ and command/", "hint": "CLAUDE.md's 'spot-check a sample with grep before relying on them' combined with blast's own retained_note ('Which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified') and completeness verdict 'partial' with hidden:134 — that admission is what made me verify rather than transcribe"}
  ],
  "q4_value": "retained_via_interfaces on sense_blast. The literal core of the ticket was 'find holders whose field is a locally-declared interface, so the file never imports nomad and never names *Server' — and that field handed me volumewatcher via CSIVolumeRPC, drainer via RaftApplier, the three schedulers via Planner, auth via Encrypter, and the whole client-side RPCer chain, each with a carrier and a containment chain. Recovering that with grep would have meant guessing interface names I had no reason to know existed; nothing else in my toolkit inverts 'who satisfies this' into 'who retains this'.",
  "q5_improve": "Extend retention analysis to cover values reachable through bound method values and closures, and give each row the retaining field's own line rather than the struct's start line. The two things blast missed were both function-value bindings — deploymentWatcherRaftShim{apply: s.raftApply} (nomad/server.go:1161) and the Authenticator's StateFn/GetLeaderACLFn closures (nomad/server.go:476-478) — and the first is the highest-risk holder in the entire audit. index_caveat already names 'function-value passing (handlers stored as fields)' as a known blind spot; for a lifecycle-retention query that blind spot is precisely the answer. Second: a live-vs-declared flag would have saved me the RPCHandler grep, since blast presented a test-only route with the same confidence as production ones.",
  "score": 8,
  "score_rationale": "retained_via_interfaces gave me the narrowed-handle inventory that grep could not have produced without knowing the interface names in advance (Q1, Q4), but I still needed grep for field-level lines, every assignment site, the live-vs-test distinction, and the deploymentwatcher subsystem it missed entirely — plus a truncated graph call that self-reported 'complete' (Q1 wrong, Q2), which is squarely the 'faster, but I needed fallbacks to finish' band."
}

